"a.心神狂乱的 【英】 adj. 心神狂乱的(mentally confused; distressed) 【考】 troubled : distraught / covetous : rapacious(程度:不安的→狂乱 的/贪婪的→十分贪婪 的)反义词：composed(镇 定的) 【记】 由distract(分散注意 , 发狂)变化而来 【例】 I tried to console the distraught family in the hospital. adj. (因感情纠葛)心神狂乱的 = distressed; 精神错乱的 = insane 【记】是distract(v 使精神错乱; 使不安)的变体dis向四面八方, traught读: 撞他－开着一辆破车到处乱撞－肯定是因为失恋了而心神狂乱的 【类】troubled: distraught = covetous: rapacious十分不安的是狂乱的 = 十分贪婪的是十分贪婪的 【反】composed(adj 镇定的) 【记】源自distract 心烦意乱，精神不集中，将u去掉，g=c就是distract；dis + 音：创她，创伤了她的心灵 distraught (adj.)  late 14c., alteration (Englishing) of earlier distract (perhaps by association with other past participle forms in -ght, such as caught, bought, brought), mid-14c., past participle of distracten ""derange the intellect of, drive mad"" (see distract)."
